<h1>orgmode-daedalus</h1>

<p>
A parser and pretty-printer for the <a href="https://orgmode.org">Org-Mode</a> document format.
</p>
<ul>
<li>Parsing is implemented using the Galois <a href="https://github.com/GaloisInc/daedalus">Daedalus</a> parser (which permits
generation of C, C++, and Rust parsers as well).
<ul>
<li>Parsing errors are reported via the <a href="https://hackage.haskell.org/package/diagnose">diagnose</a> package.</li>
</ul></li>
<li>Pretty-printing is implemented using the <a href="https://hackage.haskell.org/package/sayable">sayable</a> package.</li>
</ul>
<p>
Development and usage is supported by the <a href="https://github.com/GaloisInc/eng">eng</a> tool. Install this tool and type <span class="code">eng</span> in this directory for more information.
</p>

<h1>OrgMode support details</h1>

<p>
Note that structural and markup parsing are distinct operations: markup is parsed
entirely within each individual structural element.
</p>
<h2>Structural parsing [41%]</h2>

