<h1>Alternatives</h1>

<h2>Parsing</h2>

<ul>
<li><a href="https://hackage.haskell.org/package/org-mode">org-mode</a>
<ul>
<li>list items can only be <b><i>simple text</i></b>.</li>
<li>not responsive to github engagement</li>
<li>supports output as minimal org source, but no pretty-printing</li>
</ul></li>
<li><a href="https://hackage.haskell.org/package/org-parser">org-parser</a>
<ol>
<li>May be <b>more</b> complete than this library.</li>
<li>Uses a templating system (ondim) for pretty-printing (exporting)
to different formats.</li>
</ol></li>
<li><a href="https://hackage.haskell.org/package/orgmode">orgmode</a>
<ul>
<li>built on Parsec library</li>
</ul></li>
<li><a href="https://hackage.haskell.org/package/orgmode-parse">orgmode-parse</a>
<ul>
<li>built on <code>Attoparsec</code></li>
<li>no <s>normal,</s> markup or block support</li>
<li>no <u>pretty-printing</u></li>
</ul></li>
</ul>

